  "instructions": [
    "In a large bowl, whisk together soy sauce, brown sugar, rice vinegar, garlic, and ginger. Add the sirloin steak tips and marinate for at least 30 minutes, or up to 2 hours in the refrigerator.",
    "Preheat the robata-grill to 400°F.",
    "Thread the marinated sirloin steak tips onto skewers, leaving a small space between each piece.",
    "Grill the skewers for 8-10 minutes per side, or until cooked to your desired level of doneness.",
    "Meanwhile, mix together the toasted sesame seeds, green onions, and chilies in a small bowl.",
    "Brush the skewers with sesame oil and sprinkle the sesame seed mixture evenly over the top.",
    "Serve the skewers hot with additional green onions and toasted sesame seeds, if desired."
